title: Handles the backend
comment: SIPdroid prefers to setup using pbxes to manage the inbound/outbound calling. At first I was horrified at the prospect of setting this up, but they automate the process in the app. You give them the account info so they can fwd it to the right addresses, etc, and it sets up a pbxes account with your google infomation.  Near as I understand, this works by placing calls in the SIP protocol, and using pbxes to convert them to jabber and work with Google Talk. This allows you to make outbound calls similar to how you can do it from gmail.  If you look around in the pbxes dash, you can see what the SIPdroid app has autopopulated, and why it requires the info it does. Overally, the GUI may not be fantastic, but the app is quick, responsive, and does an incredible job facilitating this for users new to VoIP.
